version_description: • Fixed Climate calendar bug
• Fixed registration bug
• Fixed minor heater issue.

• New: WatchOS 2 support
• New: Use touch ID to unlock your Volvo and start your engine remotely
• New: Unlock your Volvo and start the engine remotely from your watch with WatchOS 2 (requires PIN on watch)
• New: 100 days journal log

• New: Quick actions - 3D-touch on iPhone 6s/6s Plus
• New: Widgets - Interact with your Volvo from Today Widget in Notification Center
• New: Calendar card - Send your calendar destination to your Volvo navigation system 
• Improved: Driving journal

• Improved: Calendar card performance
• Fixed: Apple Watch text truncation

New in 4.0
• Visual facelift
• New tab-bar navigation
• Improved map experience
• Owners manual integration

We have read through your feedback and this release fixes most of the issues that have been reported, including:

• Bug showing wrong address for the car
• Crash that could happen when categorizing a trip on an iPad.
• Crash that could occur when sending destination to car.
• Issues with the calendar card

Thank you for using Volvo On Call! 
If you encounter any issues please contact us at vocapp@volvocars.com

In this version, Siri support was added to Volvo On Call, requires iOS 10.3+.  You can try the following commands:

• How much fuel is left in my car?
• Is my car locked/unlocked?
• Lock/unlock my car
• Flash the lights on my car

We have also read through your feedback and this release includes the following improvements:

• Driving journal is now accessible from the Home tab
• Implemented swiping between trips in driving journal

Thank you for using Volvo On Call! 
If you encounter any issues please contact us at vocapp@volvocars.com
